answerText: The Expedition of Humphrey Clinker[10] The Expedition of Humphrey Clinker is one of this man's picaresque novels. His other works detail the "Adventures of" characters like Ferdinand Count Fathom and Peregrine Pickle.

question: Question: This novel is comprised of letters from characters like Tabitha Bramble and Jery Melford, but not the title character. For 10 points each: [10] Name this work in which the title character is taken in by the traveling family of Matthew Bramble, who turns out to be the title character's father.
